<h1>General Orders</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationRight">Head Quarters, Cambridge, March 22nd 1776.</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
<table class="password"><tr>
		<td class="parole">Parole Grafton.</td>
		<td class="csigns">Countersign,<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0001" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></td>
	      </tr></table>

</div>
<p>The Colonel of Artillery, Quarter Master General, Commissary General and Commissary of Ordnance stores, to make out exact Returns of all military Stores, Provisions &amp;c. &amp;c. now in Boston, Cambridge, Roxbury, Dorchester Heights, and Forts &amp;c. adjacentThis must be done in the correctest manner, and when finishd and signd, delivered by the proper Officer of each department, to the Commander in Chief.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0002" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
<p>The Provost Marshal is forthwith to remove with his prisoners, to BostonThe prisoners of war, and John Stevens, are by his Excellencys order, to be put into Boston goal.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0003" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0003-ptr">3</a></p>
<p>The Majors of Brigade, to order the Adjutants to be punctual in delivering their weekly returns at orderly time to morrow.</p>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0379-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Artemas Wards orderly book gives the countersign for this date as Hancock (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Massachusetts Historical Society, Boston ]">MHi</span>).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0390-0002" class="document">Inventory of British Stores Left in Boston, 20 Mar.</a>,<span class="choice deletion" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Deleted: ' printed below as' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2014-12-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]"><img alt="deletion" src="images/deletion_mark-trans.png" style="border:none;vertical-align: text-bottom; padding-right:2px"/></span> an enclosure to <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0390-0001" class="document">GW to Hancock, 24 Mar. 1776</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0409-0002" class="document">Return of British Ordnance Stores Left in Boston, 22 Mar.</a>, printed as an enclosure to <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0409-0001" class="document">GW to Hancock, 27 Mar. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-03-03-02-pb-0512">[512]</span>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0379-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>John Stevens, a Loyalist from Charlestown, Mass., later settled at St. John, New Brunswick. He is not to be confused with John Stevens (17481792) of Concord, Mass., who was arrested in May 1777 for selling boycotted goods and was subsequently released by order of the General Court. See <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ J. L. Sibley et al. &lt;i&gt;Sibleys Harvard Graduates: Biographical Sketches of Those Who Attended Harvard College&lt;/i&gt;. 18 vols. to date. Boston, 1873. ]">Sibley and Shipton, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Harvard Graduates</span></span>, 16:42627.</p>

</div>
